KATSINA – The Executive Director Katsina state Pilgrims Welfare Board, Alhaji Suleiman Nuhu Kuki has monitored the ongoing pilgrims orientation workshop exercises in Kankia and Dutsinma zonal Pilgrims offices, urging the intending Pilgrims to avail themselves with the knowledge been taught to make 2022 hajj exercise a success. Kuki made this assertion while addressing the intending Pilgrims at the two centres visited at the weekend. According to him, about 2,146 seats have been allocated to the State for this year’s Hajj operation, appealing to the intending Pilgrims to ensure the completion of their payment soonest. -Advertisement- The Pilgrims Board boss however explained that the increase on Hajj fare followed the hike in air fare and exchange rates of the dollars to the naira. He further informed the intending pilgrims that those above the age of 65 years would not be eligible to performed this year’s Hajj, While those blow the age would have to show evidence of complete vaccination in addition to PCR Covid-19 test within 74 hours before take off to the holy Land. Kuki who expressed satisfaction with the way and manner the pilgrims conducted themselves during the orientation exercise in the two zonal centres, urged them to get clarification wherever needed to get the required knowledge and understanding of the exercise. He also commended the preachers for their efforts in handling the workshop programme, calling on them to ensure that all intending pilgrims from the state have knowledge of all necessary Hajj doctrines.